## Pitfall 4: Infinite Scroll Without Virtualisation on Long Lists

**What developers do:**

```tsx
// ❌ After 50 fetches × 20 items = 1,000 DOM nodes. Phones start choking.
const allProducts = data?.pages.flatMap(page => page.data) ?? [];

return (
  <div>
    {allProducts.map(p => <ProductCard key={p.id} product={p} />)}
  </div>
);
```

**Why it fails:**
- Every appended item stays in the DOM forever
- 500+ complex card components causes layout thrashing during scroll
- On a 3GB RAM Android device, browser memory warnings appear around 300–500 cards

**Fix:**

```tsx
// ✅ Only render what's visible — virtual list with @tanstack/react-virtual
import { useVirtualizer } from '@tanstack/react-virtual';

const rowVirtualizer = useVirtualizer({
  count: hasNextPage ? allProducts.length + 1 : allProducts.length,
  getScrollElement: () => parentRef.current,
  estimateSize: () => 120, // estimated card height in px
  overscan: 5,
});
```

