## Pitfall 6: Triggering Multiple Simultaneous Fetches

**What developers do:**

```tsx
// ❌ If the user scrolls fast, this fires 3× before the first response arrives
useEffect(() => {
  if (nearBottom) {
    fetchNextPage(); // called 3 times, 3 duplicate requests
  }
}, [scrollPosition]);
```

**Why it fails:**
- Race conditions between simultaneous page fetches
- Duplicate API calls waste bandwidth (expensive on mobile data)
- Items may appear duplicated if responses arrive out of order

**Fix:**

```tsx
// ✅ Guard with isFetchingNextPage — TanStack Query sets this automatically
useEffect(() => {
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(([entry]) => {
    if (entry.isIntersecting && hasNextPage && !isFetchingNextPage) {
      fetchNextPage();
    }
  });
  observer.observe(sentinelRef.current);
  return () => observer.disconnect();
}, [hasNextPage, isFetchingNextPage]); // re-register when these change
```

