## Pitfall 8: No Empty State or Error State

**What developers do:**

```tsx
// ❌ Network errors silently produce an empty list
// User doesn't know if there are no products, or if something failed
return (
  <div>
    {products.map(p => <ProductCard key={p.id} product={p} />)}
  </div>
);
```

**Fix:**

```tsx
// ✅ Handle all states explicitly
if (status === 'pending') return <SkeletonGrid />;

if (status === 'error') return (
  <ErrorState
    message="Couldn't load products"
    onRetry={() => refetch()}
  />
);

if (products.length === 0) return (
  <EmptyState message="No products found. Try adjusting your filters." />
);

return (
  <>
    {products.map(p => <ProductCard key={p.id} product={p} />)}
    <div ref={sentinelRef} />
    {isFetchingNextPage && <LoadingSpinner />}
  </>
);
```

Never let an error or empty result look the same as a loaded empty list.